If somebody goes there not just for xp, but also for loot (like me ;-) ) you can increase your outcome a bit.<br>
After you killed Cynthia and you and your Pet are ok just run a bit towards the haunted tower and there are usually a few Giant skeletons around which can also drop up to 1pp. and some even con light blue to you at lvl 35 ;-)<br>
Or you could simply kill some of the Lizardmen who wander around everywhere there. They are all green but also drop a few gp's.<br>
<br>
By this I can usually make additional 1-2pp between the times Cynthia spawns. Usually killing her takes not more than 1-2 mana bubbles. So after the first kill I wander around and kill some stuff. Then I kill her again and med afterwards (I think 3 kills should be possible, but I like it safe ;-) ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(5/13/02 11:09:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Poor Cynthia</span><hr size=1> Well, since I did hit lvl 39 there now, I will leave the area soon after I got some &quot;safety xp&quot; ;-)<br>
first of all, people can tell me what they want, lvl 35 and 36 are still some kind of &quot;hell level&quot;. I gained xp *much* faster at 37 and 38 than I did at 36 for example. (I was there only for the last yellow bubble of lvl 35, but still I think even then I gained xp much slower as at 37 for example)<br>
<br>
Now, since lvl 36 I also hunted the Cyclopse regulary during the Cynthia breaks. Usually I could do 1 cyclops after 3 Cynthia kills (for the reason that I had FM shortly after i killed Cynthia then)<br>
<br>
It went pretty nice, never ever died there (even I was one time VERY close ...lost Pet to Cyclops, was OOM and had to run to lake zone...got out with 21 HPs ;-) )<br>
<br>
Now, killing Cynthia is really easy, but here's my take on the Cyclopse:<br>
<br>
- Casted Inferno shield on Pet (air)<br>
- Pulled Cyclops with Malise, sent Pet to intercept it.<br>
If Malise failed I tried again one more time, always worked latest at 2nd try, except for Tarsuk whom I once fought without malise.<br>
- Rain of Spikes<br>
- Shock of Flame (about 100dmg with Focus bracelet)<br>
- Renew summoning (Pet usually at 60-70% health now)<br>
- Rain of Spikes.<br>
- Blaze<br>
- check on Pet health....if over 50% health I simply would have casted Blaze until Cyclops started to run, then SoF to finish it.<br>
<br>
I don't have a very high intelligence, so I usually came out of the cyclops-fights with 10-20m<br>
<br>
Cynthia wouldn't have respawned yet but still I always &quot;lost&quot; 1 or 2 minutes because I wasn't at 40m and Pets till pretty hurt at the time she spawned.<br>
But since the cyclopse give better xp than cynthia the small loss of time is well worth it.<br>
Anyway...I think I got through the levels 37/38 in 5-6 hours each.<br>
And the outcome of all that cynthia killing was probably well over 1k pp. Nice combination of xp and loot I think.<br>
(gave me finally the ressources to buy some nice stuff I couldn't afford before: Stein of Moggok (200pp), crystalline Robe (100pp...pretty cheap, but got it from a guild member), 10-shot-SOW-Potion (100pp). <br>
Now I'm looking forward to do some spell-purchasing runs with the knowledge that buying the spells won't ruin me for the fist time in my Mage-career :-)<br>
<br>
Thank you Cynthia!<br>
